correctness.rationale: Multiple schema violations and factual mismatches. Key issues: (1) Nulls/placeholder values where numbers/objects are required: plasmaPower=null, supercycleDesign=null, nucleationPeriod.numericValue=null, processParameters.filmThickness.numericValue=null, conformality.aspectRatio.numericValue=null, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue=null, roughness.value.numericValue=null, filmDensity.value.numericValue=null; deviceProperties fields set to null. These violate the schema (numbers/objects expected, not null). (2) Time units wrong by 10^3: dosingTime and purgeTime use unit MilliSEC but values (0.7 and 30) are seconds from the article; they should be ~700 ms and 30000 ms. (3) Pressure set to 4 Torr (purge) while “pressure during exposure” is 6–7 Torr per article; the single pressure field should reflect deposition conditions. (4) filmThickness missing though thickness can be computed (e.g., ~95 nm for 500 cycles at 1.9 Å/cycle) or reported; leaving it null violates schema. (5) Electrical properties inconsistent with the captured process: resistivity 0.0014 ohm·m corresponds to 0.14 ohm·cm and does not match the article’s best 1.4×10^-3 ohm·cm; also those low resistivities were for Ga-doped films at higher temperatures with TMG pulses, but the process lacks Ga precursor and uses 130 °C. (6) Carrier density unit/magnitude incorrect: given as 1.2e20 C/m^3 (wrong unit and no cm^-3→m^-3 conversion) and again only applicable to Ga-doped films. (7) Mobility 25 cm^2/Vs likewise corresponds to Ga-doped films, not the undoped ZnO process described in this record. (8) Unsubstantiated materials data: crystallinity “polycrystalline” by XRD, roughness by AFM, density by XRR, elemental concentrations and atomic ratio “1:1” are not reported in the article; providing values or methods not in the source breaks traceability. (9) Uniformity “10%” not supported; the article only mentions sample-to-sample thickness variation of 10–20 Å, not across-substrate uniformity. (10) Minor: reactor fields set to “Not Found” despite the article stating a hot-wall reactor; deliveryMethod left “Not Found.” Corrections needed: fix time units/values; use exposure pressure (6–7 Torr) or specify both; populate filmThickness; either add Ga precursor and correct temperature if reporting Ga-doped properties, or replace electrical properties with undoped values consistent with 130 °C; correct resistivity units (ohm·cm vs ohm·m); fix carrier density unit to PER-M3 with proper conversion; remove or substantiate crystallinity/AFM/XRR/composition; remove null fields or supply valid numeric values per schema.

completeness.rationale: Major incompleteness and schema issues. Multiple processes described in the article are not captured (only one process provided): (i) ZnO on PET at 130 C, (ii) ZnO on PET at >130 C using an Al2O3 buffer layer (TMA/H2O; 0.2 s exposures; purge >15 s), (iii) Ga-doped ZnO via TMG pulse substitution (e.g., 1.5% Ga cycles) with results at 130–210 C, and (iv) growth on glass/sapphire/Si at various temperatures. Several fields violate the schema or are null/placeholder: plasmaPower=None, supercycleDesign=None, filmThickness numericValue=None (twice), nucleationPeriod numericValue=None, conformality.aspectRatio numericValue=None, elementalConcentration numericValue=None, roughness numericValue=None, filmDensity numericValue=None, many "Not Found" placeholders. Time units are wrong: dosing and purge times use MilliSEC but values are in seconds (0.7 s and 30 s recorded as 0.7 ms and 30 ms; should be 700 ms and 30000 ms). Pressure only reflects purge pressure (4 Torr); exposure pressure (6–7 Torr) omitted. Flow rates are assigned (100 sccm) to precursor and co-reactant without support; units set to SCM-PER-MIN do not match sccm. Several values are untraceable or incorrect: crystallinity "polycrystalline by XRD" not reported; atomic ratio 1:1 not reported; uniformity set to 10% is not supported (article reports 10–20 Å sample-to-sample variation, not across-substrate uniformity); resistivity is wrong by unit conversion (reported best PET film 1.4×10^-3 Ω·cm = 1.4×10^-5 Ω·m, but 0.0014 Ω·m is entered); carrier density uses C-PER-M3 and magnitude is incorrect (should use PER-M3; e.g., ~2×10^20 cm^-3 ≈ 2×10^26 m^-3). Film thickness is reported in the article (~1500 Å for some resistivity measurements) but left empty; delivery method is described (automated manifold, pulsed exposures, N2 carrier) but marked "Not Found". Supercycle design for Ga doping (e.g., 1.5% TMG-substituted pulses) is not represented. To improve: add separate process instances for (a) undoped ZnO at 130 C on PET, (b) ZnO on PET with Al2O3 buffer at >130 C (include TMA/H2O timings), (c) Ga-doped ZnO with 1.5% TMG substitution at 190–210 C (include supercycle design), and (d) films on glass; correct units (times in ms; resistivity in Ω·m; carrier density in PER-M3 with correct magnitude); fill film thickness (~150 nm when stated); include both purge and exposure pressures; remove unsupported fields (crystallinity, atomic ratio, uniformity) or replace with traceable values if reported.
